The paper deals with real-time synchronization in multiprocessor systems, which is a topic that falls under the category of operating systems (cs.OS). The paper also discusses the computational complexity of the problem, which suggests that it could be categorized under distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC) or data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). The paper also presents algorithms and tradeoffs, which could place it under machine learning (cs.LG) or control systems (cs.SY).
